<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1679,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">Description</emphasis>
. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Walter" box="[406,564,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Walter, C. (1911) Hydracarina der Aru-Inseln. In: Merton, H. (Ed.), Ergebnisse einer zoolog. Forschungsreise in den sudostlichen Molukken, 2, pp. 207 - 222." type="journal article" year="1911">Walter (1911)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[626,772,1751,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 13, 484 - 594, 595 - 738." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets (1935)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional characters: Male idiosoma 834 long and 753 wide, female idiosoma 899 long and 826 wide. Genital field: male 259 long, and 316 wide, female 267 long and 332 wide. The male has an oblique anterior margin of the genital valve, in the female this margin is straight with a short medial extension. The pre-genital sclerite of the male is rhomboid in the male and triangular in the female. The configuration of the mediodorsal plates dg5 and dg6 (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Harvey" box="[839,979,1896,1920]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Harvey, M. S. (1988) New species of the water mite family Hydryphantidae (Acarina) from the Northern Territory, Australia. The Beagle, Records of the Northern Territory of Arts and Sciences, 5, 17 - 26." type="journal article" year="1988">Harvey1988</bibRefCitation>
) of both sexes is asymmetrical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1679,2029]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="71" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Jin" box="[322,520,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Jin, D. &amp; Guo, Z. (1993) [A new species of Mamersinae, a first record subfamily of water mites from China (Acari: Hydryphantidae.] Journal of Guizhou Agricultural College, Supplement 12, 61 - 63. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="1993">Jin &amp; Guo (1993)</bibRefCitation>
stated that, in describing 
<taxonomicName authority="Jin &amp; Guo, 1993" authorityName="Jin &amp; Guo" authorityYear="1993" box="[808,1154,1932,1957]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paddicola">
<emphasis box="[808,957,1932,1956]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">M. paddicola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jin" box="[964,1154,1932,1957]" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" refString="Jin, D. &amp; Guo, Z. (1993) [A new species of Mamersinae, a first record subfamily of water mites from China (Acari: Hydryphantidae.] Journal of Guizhou Agricultural College, Supplement 12, 61 - 63. [in Chinese]" type="journal article" year="1993">Jin &amp; Guo, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the new species differed in the presence of two pairs of posterolateral plates. However, they overlooked 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1911" box="[1070,1168,1969,1992]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="1" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis box="[1070,1168,1969,1992]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="70">M. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species they did not mention in the paper. Their illustrations match the description of the latter species, and we therefore propose to synonymize 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jin &amp; Guo" authorityYear="1993" box="[296,448,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paddicola">
<emphasis box="[296,448,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">M. paddicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walter" authorityYear="1911" box="[517,615,152,176]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Mamersa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rouxi">
<emphasis box="[517,615,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">M. rouxi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The differences in the shape of the pre-genital sclerite and the genital valves was not mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets" box="[486,629,188,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="71" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 13, 484 - 594, 595 - 738." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets (1935)</bibRefCitation>
. The species is new for the fauna of 
<collectingCountry box="[1042,1145,188,213]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. It has been found on the Aru Islands, 
<collectingRegion box="[295,388,224,248]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[442,543,223,248]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[558,671,223,248]" name="Indonesia" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
, Wiles pers. comm.), 
<collectingCountry box="[915,982,223,248]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1036,1136,223,248]" name="Thailand" pageId="2" pageNumber="71">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(present study).
</paragraph>
